8.1 Scheduler State Machine

State LISTENING:

· Receive 20ms audio chunk
· Update LDVS latent state
· Incrementally decode text (CTC streaming)
· Run predictive head to precompute future speech chunks
· Cache predictions with confidence scores
· On turn boundary: LSR → SPEAKING

State SPEAKING:

· Generate response tokens
· If cache matches and confidence > threshold: play cached audio
· Else: generate on-the-fly
· On response complete → LISTENING

8.2 Predictive Caching Algorithm

```python
cache = deque(maxlen=10)

def listening_step(audio_chunk, partial_text):
    z = ldvs_forward(z_prev, audio_chunk)
    
    for tau in [200, 300, 400, 500]:
        z_future = predictive_head(z, partial_text, tau)
        speech = speech_decoder_stream(z_future)
        confidence = compute_confidence(z_future, partial_text)
        if confidence > 0.7:
            cache.append((tau, speech, confidence))
    return z

def speaking_step(response_token):
    if cache and matches(cache[0], response_token):
        return cache.popleft().audio
    else:
        z = ldvs_forward(z_prev, text_encoder(response_token))
        return speech_decoder_stream(z)
```

